<node id="PGRP-SD" name="peptidoglycan recognition proteins" maxvalue="1">
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="DAP"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="PMID:18304640"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>PGRP- SD presumably recognizes Diaminopimelic acid (DAP)-type PGNs from Gram-negative bacteria, thereby activating the Toll pathway (Leone et al., 2008). 
In addition,  flies with the PGRP-SA; PGRP-SD double mutation are highly susceptible to Gram-positive bacteria infection (Bischoff et al., 2004)</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="859" y="209" width="68" height="35" backgroundColor="#ffffcc" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
