<node id="GNBP3" name="Gram- negative binding protein 3" maxvalue="1">
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="Fungi"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <linklist>
      <link xlink:href="PMID:17190605"/>
      <link xlink:href="PMID:19590012"/>
      <link xlink:href="http://flybase.org/reports/FBgn0040321.html"/>
    </linklist>
    <comment>For fungi recognition, over-expression of GNBP3 triggers the Toll pathway, resulting in a constitutive expression of 
Drosomycin in the absence of an immune challenge (Gottar et al., 2006; Buchon et al., 2009). 
Among the GNBP, GNBP3 shows the greatest degree of similarity to lepidopteran (1,3)- glucan recognition proteins and was therefore a good candidate for being a fungal-specific sensor. 
</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="577" y="211" width="60" height="35" backgroundColor="#ffffcc" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
